{
  "easy": {
    "title": "Build a Navigation Menu with Links",
    "description": "Create a simple navigation menu with at least 4 links: Home, About, Services, Contact. Use a mix of absolute and relative URLs. Style the links so they have hover effects (color change and underline).",
    "starterCode": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Navigation Menu</title>\n  <style>\n    /* Add your styles here */\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <nav>\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"index.html\">Home</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"about.html\">About</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"services.html\">Services</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"contact.html\">Contact</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </nav>\n</body>\n</html>",
    "solution": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Navigation Menu</title>\n  <style>\n    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }\n    body {\n      font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n      background: #f8f9fa;\n      padding: 30px;\n    }\n    nav {\n      background: #2c3e50;\n      padding: 15px 25px;\n      border-radius: 10px;\n    }\n    nav ul {\n      list-style: none;\n      display: flex;\n      gap: 30px;\n    }\n    nav a {\n      color: #ecf0f1;\n      text-decoration: none;\n      font-size: 18px;\n      padding: 8px 0;\n      position: relative;\n      transition: color 0.3s;\n    }\n    nav a::after {\n      content: '';\n      position: absolute;\n      bottom: 0;\n      left: 0;\n      width: 0;\n      height: 2px;\n      background: #3498db;\n      transition: width 0.3s;\n    }\n    nav a:hover {\n      color: #3498db;\n    }\n    nav a:hover::after {\n      width: 100%;\n    }\n    /* External link style */\n    nav a[href^=\"http\"]::before {\n      content: '↗';\n      margin-right: 4px;\n    }\n    nav a:visited {\n      color: #bb8fce;\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <nav>\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"index.html\">Home</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"about.html\">About</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"services.html\">Services</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"contact.html\">Contact</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://github.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GitHub</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </nav>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
  "medium": {
    "title": "Create a Table of Contents with Anchor Links",
    "description": "Build a long 'article' page (use lorem ipsum paragraphs) with a table of contents at the top. Each TOC item should link to its corresponding section. Include a 'Back to Top' link after each section. Style the page for readability.",
    "starterCode": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Article with Table of Contents</title>\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: 'Georgia', serif; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Understanding Web Development</h1>\n  \n  <div class=\"toc\">\n    <h2>Table of Contents</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <!-- Add TOC links here -->\n    </ul>\n  </div>\n\n  <section id=\"intro\">\n    <h2>Introduction</h2>\n    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet...</p>\n    <a href=\"#\">Back to Top</a>\n  </section>\n\n  <!-- Add more sections -->\n</body>\n</html>",
    "solution": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Article with Table of Contents</title>\n  <style>\n    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }\n    body {\n      font-family: 'Georgia', serif;\n      line-height: 1.8;\n      max-width: 800px;\n      margin: 0 auto;\n      padding: 40px 20px;\n      color: #333;\n    }\n    h1 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px; color: #1a1a2e; font-size: 2.5em; }\n    h2 { color: #16213e; margin-top: 40px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-bottom: 2px solid #e94560; padding-bottom: 8px; }\n    p { margin-bottom: 16px; text-indent: 1.5em; }\n\n    .toc {\n      background: #f8f9fa;\n      border: 1px solid #dee2e6;\n      border-radius: 10px;\n      padding: 25px 30px;\n      margin-bottom: 40px;\n    }\n    .toc h2 { margin-top: 0; border-bottom: none; }\n    .toc ul { list-style: none; }\n    .toc li { margin: 10px 0; }\n    .toc a {\n      text-decoration: none;\n      color: #e94560;\n      font-size: 18px;\n      transition: color 0.3s;\n    }\n    .toc a:hover { color: #c23152; text-decoration: underline; }\n\n    .back-to-top {\n      display: inline-block;\n      margin-top: 10px;\n      color: #666;\n      text-decoration: none;\n      font-size: 14px;\n      transition: color 0.3s;\n    }\n    .back-to-top:hover { color: #e94560; }\n\n    section { margin-bottom: 30px; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Understanding Web Development</h1>\n\n  <div class=\"toc\">\n    <h2>Table of Contents</h2>\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"#intro\">Introduction</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#html\">HTML Basics</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#css\">CSS Fundamentals</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#js\">JavaScript Essentials</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"#conclusion\">Conclusion</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </div>\n\n  <section id=\"intro\">\n    <h2>Introduction</h2>\n    <p>Web development is the process of building websites and applications for the internet. It encompasses everything from simple static pages to complex dynamic platforms.</p>\n    <p>The three core technologies of web development are HTML (structure), CSS (presentation), and JavaScript (interactivity). Each plays a vital role in creating modern web experiences.</p>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"back-to-top\">⬆ Back to Top</a>\n  </section>\n\n  <section id=\"html\">\n    <h2>HTML Basics</h2>\n    <p>HTML (HyperText Markup Language) provides the structural foundation of web pages. It uses tags and attributes to define headings, paragraphs, links, images, and other content elements.</p>\n    <p>Semantic HTML elements like &lt;header&gt;, &lt;nav&gt;, &lt;main&gt;, and &lt;footer&gt; give meaning to content structure, improving accessibility and SEO.</p>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"back-to-top\">⬆ Back to Top</a>\n  </section>\n\n  <section id=\"css\">\n    <h2>CSS Fundamentals</h2>\n    <p>CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) controls the visual presentation of HTML elements. It handles colors, typography, spacing, layout, and responsive design.</p>\n    <p>With CSS, you can create complex layouts using Flexbox and Grid, add animations, and ensure your pages look great on all devices through media queries.</p>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"back-to-top\">⬆ Back to Top</a>\n  </section>\n\n  <section id=\"js\">\n    <h2>JavaScript Essentials</h2>\n    <p>JavaScript adds interactivity and dynamic behavior to web pages. It can manipulate the DOM, handle user events, communicate with servers, and build full-featured applications.</p>\n    <p>Modern JavaScript (ES6+) provides powerful features like arrow functions, promises, async/await, and modules that make development more efficient.</p>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"back-to-top\">⬆ Back to Top</a>\n  </section>\n\n  <section id=\"conclusion\">\n    <h2>Conclusion</h2>\n    <p>Mastering HTML, CSS, and JavaScript is the foundation of web development. Each technology has its role, and they work together to create the web as we know it today.</p>\n    <p>Continue learning and building projects to strengthen your understanding of these essential web technologies.</p>\n    <a href=\"#\" class=\"back-to-top\">⬆ Back to Top</a>\n  </section>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
  "hard": {
    "title": "Build a Multi-Page Resource Directory with Link Relationships",
    "description": "Create a two-page mini site: a directory page and a detail page. The directory lists resources with links to the detail page using query parameters (?id=1). The detail page extracts the id and shows corresponding information (use JavaScript to simulate this). Include proper rel attributes, breadcrumb navigation, back links, and semantic HTML.",
    "starterCode": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Resource Directory</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Resource Directory</h1>\n  <div class=\"resource-list\">\n    <!-- Add resource entries with links to detail page -->\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>",
    "solution": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Resource Directory</title>\n  <style>\n    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }\n    body {\n      font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n      max-width: 900px;\n      margin: 0 auto;\n      padding: 30px 20px;\n      background: #f4f6f8;\n    }\n    h1 { color: #1a1a2e; margin-bottom: 30px; text-align: center; }\n    .resource-grid {\n      display: grid;\n      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(250px, 1fr));\n      gap: 20px;\n    }\n    .resource-card {\n      background: white;\n      border-radius: 12px;\n      padding: 25px;\n      box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);\n      transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;\n    }\n    .resource-card:hover {\n      transform: translateY(-4px);\n      box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n    }\n    .resource-card h3 { color: #16213e; margin-bottom: 8px; }\n    .resource-card p { color: #64748b; margin-bottom: 15px; font-size: 14px; }\n    .resource-card a {\n      display: inline-block;\n      color: #2563eb;\n      text-decoration: none;\n      font-weight: 600;\n      transition: color 0.3s;\n    }\n    .resource-card a:hover { color: #1d4ed8; }\n    .resource-card .external-link::after {\n      content: ' ↗';\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <nav aria-label=\"Breadcrumb\" style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\">\n    <a href=\"#\" style=\"color:#64748b;text-decoration:none;\">Home</a>\n    <span style=\"color:#94a3b8;\"> / </span>\n    <span style=\"color:#1e293b;\">Resources</span>\n  </nav>\n\n  <h1>📚 Resource Directory</h1>\n\n  <div class=\"resource-grid\">\n    <div class=\"resource-card\">\n      <h3>HTML Documentation</h3>\n      <p>Official HTML documentation from MDN Web Docs covering all elements and attributes.</p>\n      <a href=\"?id=1\" class=\"internal-link\">View Details →</a>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"resource-card\">\n      <h3>CSS Reference</h3>\n      <p>Complete CSS reference with properties, selectors, and examples.</p>\n      <a href=\"?id=2\" class=\"internal-link\">View Details →</a>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"resource-card\">\n      <h3>JavaScript Guide</h3>\n      <p>Modern JavaScript tutorial from basics to advanced concepts.</p>\n      <a href=\"?id=3\" class=\"internal-link\">View Details →</a>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"resource-card\">\n      <h3>Free Web Design Course</h3>\n      <p>External resource offering free web design and development courses.</p>\n      <a href=\"https://www.freecodecamp.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"external-link\">Visit Site</a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <section id=\"resource-detail\" style=\"display:none; margin-top:40px; background:white; border-radius:12px; padding:30px; box-shadow:0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);\">\n    <a href=\"#\" id=\"back-link\" style=\"display:inline-block; margin-bottom:20px; color:#64748b; text-decoration:none;\">← Back to Directory</a>\n    <h2 id=\"detail-title\"></h2>\n    <p id=\"detail-description\" style=\"color:#475569;line-height:1.7;\"></p>\n    <p id=\"detail-url\"></p>\n  </section>\n\n  <script>\n    const resources = {\n      1: { title: 'HTML Documentation', description: 'The MDN Web Docs HTML documentation is the definitive resource for learning HTML. It covers every HTML element, attribute, and concept with examples and browser compatibility information.', url: 'https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML' },\n      2: { title: 'CSS Reference', description: 'A comprehensive CSS reference covering properties, selectors, at-rules, functions, and data types. Includes practical examples and browser support tables.', url: 'https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Reference' },\n      3: { title: 'JavaScript Guide', description: 'The JavaScript Guide introduces fundamental concepts including variables, data types, functions, objects, classes, promises, and modules. Suitable for beginners and intermediate learners.', url: 'https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide' }\n    };\n\n    const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);\n    const id = params.get('id');\n    if (id && resources[id]) {\n      const res = resources[id];\n      document.getElementById('detail-title').textContent = res.title;\n      document.getElementById('detail-description').textContent = res.description;\n      document.getElementById('detail-url').innerHTML = '<a href=\"' + res.url + '\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Visit Official Site ↗</a>';\n      document.getElementById('resource-detail').style.display = 'block';\n      document.getElementById('back-link').href = window.location.pathname;\n    }\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
